    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tools made from a flat board attached to a handle, often studded with nails, coins, or the like, used for pounding, driving, and dressing the reeds or straws into place during thatching.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
